column2: Question
If the election for governor were being held today, and the candidates were Republican Brian Kemp, Democrat Stacey Abrams, Libertarian Shane Hazel and Independent Al Bartel, for whom would you vote?
If the election for U.S. Senate were being held today, and the candidates were Republican Herschel Walker, Democrat Raphael Warnock and Libertarian Chase Oliver, for whom would you vote?
If the election for lieutenant governor were being held today, and the candidates were Republican Burt Jones, Democrat Charlie Bailey and Libertarian Ryan Graham, for whom would you vote?
If the election for secretary of state were being held today, and the candidates were Republican Brad Raffensperger, Democrat Bee Nguyen and Libertarian Ted Metz, for whom would you vote?
Do you think things in the nation are generally headed in the right direction, or do you think things are off on the wrong track?
If the election were today, would you want to see the Republican Party or the Democratic Party win control of the U.S. Congress?
Do you approve or disapprove of the way Joe Biden is handling his job as president?
Do you approve or disapprove of the way Brian Kemp is handling his job as governor?
Do you approve or disapprove of the way Raphael Warnock is handling his job as U.S. Senator?
How much confidence do you currently have in the U.S. Supreme Court?
Do you support or oppose the U.S. Supreme Court’s ruling overturning the 1973 Roe v. Wade decision which guaranteed the right to an abortion?

The Georgia Legislature passed a law in 2019 that would ban most abortions after fetal cardiac activity is detected, as early as 6 weeks of pregnancy. Now that the Supreme Court has overturned Roe, this law is expected to go into effect soon. Do you support or oppose this law?
Some state lawmakers say they want to ban all abortions in Georgia. Would you support or oppose such a ban?
Are you more likely to vote for a candidate who wants to protect access to abortion, wants to limit access to abortion, or does a candidate's position on abortion not make a difference in your vote?
How important is rising cost of gas and groceries in deciding how you will vote in the midterm election this November?
How important is gun violence in deciding how you will vote in the midterm election this November?
How important are taxes in deciding how you will vote in the midterm election this November?
How important is abortion in deciding how you will vote in the midterm election this November?
How important is immigration in deciding how you will vote in the midterm election this November?
The Georgia Legislature passed a law this year that allows those 21 and older to carry a concealed weapon in public without a license. Do you support or oppose this law?
How much of an impact have rising prices had on your day-to-day life?

column3: Noticeable, but not significantly negative impact

column2: A special congressional committee is investigating the storming of the U.S. Capitol that occurred on January 6, 2021. How closely are you following news about the work of this committee?
How much of the responsibility, if any, do you think former President Donald Trump bears for the storming of the U.S. Capitol on January 6, 2021?
If a political candidate for office says they believe the 2020 presidential election was stolen from Trump, are you more or less likely to vote for that candidate, or would it not make a difference?
